cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about using deep learning for 3D segmentation of fluorescence microscopy images. The most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as it deals with image analysis and segmentation. The use of deep learning also suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The generation of synthetic volumes using adversarial networks suggests it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the application of the method to microscopy data suggests it could belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
